==Swedish==

===Etymology===
*Since Old Swedish ''öl'' with the same meaning. From a common Germnanic root. Probably related to Latin ''[[alumen]]'' "[[alum]]"
*Same as 1.
*Same as 1 due to the custom of beer being served at feasts

===Noun===
'''öl'''

# ''(neuter gender, uncountable)'' [[beer]]
#: ''Det här var ett riktigt gott '''öl'''''.
#:"This was was a really good (kind of) beer."
# ''(common gender, countable)'' beer
#: ''Det här är vår sista '''öl'''.''.
#:"his is our last beeer".
# ''(in compund nouns, archaic)'' feast
#: ''Med anledning av landsfiskal Axelssons hastiga bortgång kommer '''gravöl''' att hållas på lördag eftermiddag.''
#:"Due to sheriff Axelssons sudden departure, funeral arrangements (literally "funeral feast") will be held on Saturday afternoon."

